To determine the six-month risk free rate, we will use the following formula:

$$ \begin{aligned}
 \dfrac{\text{$F_{t}$}}{\text{$S_{0}$}} &= \dfrac{\text{1}+\text{$R_{FC}$}}{1+\text{$R_{US}$}}\\[10pt]
\end{aligned}$$

Where: &nbsp;
$F_{t}$ =  forward exchange rate for settlement at a given time &nbsp;
$R_{US}$ = Nominal risk-free rate of U.S. &nbsp;
$R_{FC}$ = Nominal risk-free rate of a foreign country &nbsp;
$S_{0}$ = Spot Exchange Rate

First, we will determine the six-month risk free rate in Great Britain:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{$R_{FC}$} &= \left(\dfrac{\text{$F_{180}$}-\text{$S_{0}$}}{\text{$S_{0}$}}\right)+\text{$R_{US}$}\\[15pt]
&= \left(\dfrac{\text{£ 0.5929}-\text{£ 0.5920}}{\text{£ 0.5920}}\right)+\text{0.013}\\[15pt]
&= \left(\dfrac{\text{£ 0.0009}}{\text{£ 0.5920}}\right)+\text{0.013}\\[15pt]
&= 0.0015+\text{0.013}\\
&=\boxed{\text{0.0145 or 1.45\%}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
The six-month risk free rate in Great Britain is **1.45%**.

Next, we will determine the six-month risk free rate in Japan:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{$R_{FC}$} &= \left(\dfrac{\text{$F_{180}$}-\text{$S_{0}$}}{\text{$S_{0}$}}\right)+\text{$R_{US}$}\\[15pt]
&= \left(\dfrac{\text{¥ 102.21}-\text{¥ 102.32}}{\text{¥ 102.32}}\right)+\text{0.013}\\[15pt]
&= \left(\dfrac{\text{ (¥ 0.11)}}{\text{¥ 102.32}}\right)+\text{0.013}\\[10pt]
&= (0.0011)+\text{0.013}\\
&=\boxed{\text{0.0119 or 1.19\%}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
The six-month risk free rate in Japan is **1.19%**.

Lastly, we will determine  the six-month risk free rate in Switzerland:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{$R_{FC}$} &= \left(\dfrac{\text{$F_{180}$}-\text{$S_{0}$}}{\text{$S_{0}$}}\right)+\text{$R_{US}$}\\[15pt]
&= \left(\dfrac{\text{SF 0.8779 }-\text{SF 0.8793}}{\text{SF 0.8793}}\right)+\text{0.013}\\[15pt]
&= \left(\dfrac{\text{ (SF 0.0014)}}{\text{SF 0.8793}}\right)+\text{0.013}\\[15pt]
&= (0.0016)+\text{0.013}\\
&=\boxed{\text{0.0114 or 1.14\%}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
The six-month risk free rate in Switzerland is **1.14%**.
